Class GrabActionController

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.polimi.deib.se2019.sanp4.adrenaline.controller.action.GrabActionController

    SquareVisitor

    public class GrabActionController
extends Object
implements SquareVisitor
    Responsible for handling the basic action "Grab". The instance can be used for a single grab action, due to the fact that we use a visitor pattern.
    Author:
    Alessandro Fulgini

      • execute

        public void execute()
        Executes the Grab action on the the square the player is in. See the methods visit(AmmoSquare) and visit(SpawnSquare) for the details of the performed actions depending on the square type
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - If the player is not spawned
        CancellationException - If a request to the user gets cancelled

      • visit

        public void visit(AmmoSquare square)
        Executes the Grab action on an AmmoSquare. If an AmmoCard is available on the board, the user will get the associated ammo and the powerup.

        In case the user has reached the maximum number of powerups, he will be prompted to choose a powerup to discard (among the ones he has and the one he just picked). In this request, the drawn powerup will always be the first choice.

        If there is no ammo card in the square the user will get a message notification (via RemoteView.showMessage(String, MessageType)) and the action ends.

        Specified by:
        visit in interface SquareVisitor
        Parameters:
        square - The square where the player is
        Throws:
        CancellationException - If a request to the user gets cancelled

      • visit

        public void visit(SpawnSquare square)
        Executes the Grab action on SpawnSquare. The action takes place as follows:
        1. If there are no weapons on the square the user gets notified and the action ends
        2. The user is asked to select a weapon and to pay for its cost, if he can't pay he gets notified and asked to select a weapon from the remaining ones. If the player cannot pay for any of the weapons in the square, the action ends
        3. If the player has selected a weapon and can pay for it (has already converted the necessary powerups), then the methods checks if he has reached the maximum number of weapons in his hand and asks him to discard one. The discarded card is unloaded and put into the square
        4. If the player has been able to pick a weapon, pay for its cost and made space for another weapon, then the new weapon gets loaded and added to his cards
        A CancellationException may occur in three cases:
        • When the user is asked to select a card to grab, in this case the action ends and no card is grabbed
        • When the user is paying, also here the action ends and no cards is grabbed
        • When the user is selecting a card to discard, in this case no card is discarded and the card the user chose to pick is left in the square. The player does not lose any ammo or weapons, but any powerups that have been chosen to pay will have been converted to ammo cubes
        Specified by:
        visit in interface SquareVisitor
        Parameters:
        square - The square to be visited
        Throws:
        CancellationException - If a request to the user gets cancelled
